{| class="wikitable collapsible collapsed" style="width:100%"
! Patrilineal descent
|-
|
Hussein's [[Patrilineality|patriline]], or ''[[nasab]]'', traces back to [[Hashim ibn Abd Manaf]] ([[progenitor]] of the [[Banu Hashim]]) in the line of [[Hasan ibn Ali]]. Hashim is the great-grandfather of [[Mohammad]]. [[Ali]], the [[Rashidun Caliphate|fourth Caliph]] of Islam, was married to [[Fatimah]], Mohammad's daughter, from which the Hashemites claim descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alhussein.jo/en/family-tree|title=Hashemite Ancestry|work=alhussein.jo|accessdate=10 August 2017|date=1 January 2014|language=Arabic}}</ref>
